cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with computer vision and image processing techniques to estimate optical flow in rainy scenes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves image segmentation and decomposition techniques, which fall under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). The use of a residue channel as a new data constraint involves machine learning techniques, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques to enforce the brightness constancy constraint, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
